C effects remain almost as strong as at $T=0$ and\n(ii) at high temperatures they are tremendously reinforced because of the\nformation of the new collective low-energy modes. In the dipole channel, the\nlatter effect is responsible for the \"disappearance\" of the high-frequency GDR\nor, in other words, brings the GDR to the low-energy domain.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 2 Oct 2018 19:02:43 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 27 Aug 2019 13:33:18 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-08-28"}
