tages and\ndisadvantages of using high order FD or DG schemes and leap-frog or trapezoidal\ntime integrators over different frequency ranges using a variety of measures of\nnumerical dispersion errors. Finally, we highlight the limitations of the\nsecond order accurate temporal discretizations considered.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 3 Oct 2018 13:19:29 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-06-26"}
